Control Statements
------------------
The statement or instructions are used to inform the computer to perform the task when the program is being executed.

Types of Control statement : 
----------------------------
There are 4 types of control statements : 

a. Sequential control statement
action 1------------->action 2--------------->action 3
Input         Formula Implementation          Output
                    (Process)
Ex : p,r,t      si = (p*r*t)/100          o/p : si             

b. conditional control statement
    (Decision control statement)
    i. if statement
    ii. if else statement
    iii. nested if else statement
        syntax-I: 
            if(condition){
                statement 1 to n
            }else{
                if(condition)
                    statement 1 to n
                else
                    statement 1 to n
            }
        
        syntax-II: 
            if(condition){
                if(condition)
                    statement 1 to n
                else
                    statement 1 to n
            }else{
                statement 1 to n
            }

        syntax-III : 
            if(condition){
                if(condition)
                    statement 1 to n
                else
                    statement 1 to n
            }else{
                if(condition)
                    statement 1 to n
                else
                    statement 1 to n
            }

    iv. else if ladder

c. Switch control statement
   -- Switch is mainly used for menu based programming.
   -- Switch works on the concept of cases.
      case 1 :       case 'a' :        case '+' :     
      case 2 :       case 'B' :        case '-' : 
      case 3 :       case 'C' :        case '*' :
   -- Duplicate case not allowed.
   -- Switch takes constant, variables and expressions
   -- syntax : 
        switch(constant | variable | expression){
            case 1 : ......
                     break;
            case 2 : ......
                     break;
               |       |
            default : ......
                      break;       
        }     

d. Looping control statement

